<h2>URI Event Types.</h2>
<p>
Each of these events is caused by an http request to a minimal web server, these are genarally used to generate
actions from user interfaces. This web server will normallt be running on a non standard http port so that the main
web server can still function.
</p>

<p>
The event type is <span>http://id.webbrick.co.uk/events/uri</span>
</p>
<p>
The event source will be the requested object from the http request. i.e. if the uri is typed into a browser
as http://localhost:8085/home/courtesy then the event source will be '/home/courtesy'.
</p>
<p>
The other data is gleaned from the parameters passed as part of the generating request.
</p>
